2. **`src/interchange/ini.zig`** - the parser (depends only on `bun.ast`, `bun.logger`, `bun.strings`, `std`)
3. **`src/interchange.zig`** - add re-export (depends on ini.zig existing)
4. **`src/bun.js/api/INIObject.zig`** - the binding (depends on interchange/ini.zig)
5. **`src/bun.js/api.zig`** - add re-export (depends on INIObject.zig existing)
6. **`src/bun.js/bindings/BunObject+exports.h`** - C++ X-macro entry (no Zig dependency)
7. **`src/bun.js/bindings/BunObject.cpp`** - hash table entry (depends on exports.h)
8. **`src/bun.js/api/BunObject.zig`** - 4 insertions (depends on INIObject in api.zig)
9. **`packages/bun-types/bun.d.ts`** - TypeScript types (can be done at any time)
10. **`test/js/bun/ini/ini-bun.test.ts`** - test file (done last, after the runtime builds)

After all edits, run `bun run build` to regenerate the C++ hash table from `BunObject.cpp`.

---

## Key Decisions and Tradeoffs

**1. Parser scope:** The INI parser is line-based and does not need recursive descent. This is simpler than JSON5/YAML but shares the same `Expr` AST output type.

**2. Value coercion sequence:** Quoted → skip coercion (always string). Unquoted → try boolean keywords, then null, then float, then fallback to string. This matches common INI library behavior.

**3. Section key dots:** `[a.b.c]` creates `{ a: { b: { c: {} } } }`. This matches npm/ini behavior seen in the existing `ini.test.ts`.

**4. Stringify depth limit:** INI inherently cannot represent arbitrary nesting. The stringifier supports depth 0 (root scalars) and depth 1 (one level of sections). Attempting depth 2+ throws a `TypeError` with a clear message.

**5. `exprToJS` copy:** Each format object file contains its own `exprToJS` local function (this is the existing pattern — JSON5Object, YAMLObject each have their own). Do not attempt to share it.

**6. `BlobOrStringOrBuffer` input:** Both `parse` functions in YAML and JSON5 accept `BlobOrStringOrBuffer`. The INI `parse` should do the same, enabling `Bun.INI.parse(buffer)` to work.

**7. Test file naming:** The existing `test/js/bun/ini/ini.test.ts` tests the internal package-manager INI parser. The new public API test must use a different filename (`ini-bun.test.ts`) to avoid confusion.

